{"id":"268634698_Duality_For_Modules_Over_Finite_Rings_And_Applications_To_Coding_Theory","abstract":". This paper sets a foundation for the study of linear codes over finite rings. The finite Frobenius rings are singled out as the most appropriate for coding theoretic purposes because two classical theorems of MacWilliams, the extension theorem and the MacWilliams identities, generalize from finite fields to finite Frobenius rings. It is over Frobenius rings that certain key identifications can be made between the ring and its complex characters. Introduction Since the appearance of [8] and [19], using linear codes over Z=4Z to explain the duality between the non-linear binary Kerdock and Preparata codes, there has been a revival of interest in codes defined over finite rings. This paper examines the foundations of algebraic coding theory over finite rings and singles out the finite Frobenius rings as the most appropriate rings for coding theory. Why are Frobenius rings appropriate for coding theory? Because two classical theorems of MacWilliams---the extension theorem and th...","authors":["Jay Alan Wood"],"meta":["September 1999American Journal of Mathematics 121(3)","DOI:10.1353/ajm.1999.0024"],"references":["38371955_Factorization_in_Commutative_Rings_with_Zero_Divisors","3078458_The_Z4-linearity_of_Kerdock_Preparata_Goethals_and_related_codes","2137571_A_linear_construction_for_certain_Kerdock_and_Preparata_codes","268764087_Note_on_symmetric_algebras","268500845_Morita_equivalence_and_duality_Reprint_of_the_1966_ed","268248605_A_note_on_finite_local_rings","268244989_On_Frobeniusean_algebras_I","267066127_Finite_Rings_With_Identities","266687926_A_type_of_algebraic_closure","266435940_Topological_Groups","266213736_Coding_and_Combinatorics","265939145_Selbstduale_Codes_ber_dem_Ring_der_ganzen_Zahlen_modulo_4","265481970_Monomial_extensions_of_isometries_between_codes_over_Z_m","265449854_Representation_Theory_of_Artin_Algebras","265445727_Rings_and_categories